jobs.description:
An Executive-level role accountable for the leading a range of functions to including:
- product management for the suite of Clinical and Practice Management products, covering product vision, strategy, roadmap and delivery; and financial and end-user performance; 
- software support, providing tier 1 and 2 support to General Practice, Allied Health and Specialist clinics;
- sales and account management, covering customer retention, acquisition and customer management;
- customer enablement, covering training, knowledgebase, learning aids and software deployments;
- commercial partnerships, covering third party software integrations, government and industry liaison and business development;
- finance, reporting and contracts.

Strategic interface between Group IT and the key business stakeholders in the Consumer Australia business.  

The purpose of the role - to ensure:
•	IT strategies and plans are aligned with the business strategies and goals;
•	IT delivers innovative IT systems and services that enable business process transformation; profitable business growth; and product and service innovation;
•	IT projects are delivered on time, on budget and fulfil IT’s commitment to the business; and
•	IT systems delivered are reliable, available, cost-effective and cost-efficient.
